## Key Observations for Backend Development

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The Axios client `baseURL` is hardcoded to `http://localhost:5174` (same as the Vite dev port). The actual backend server should run on a **different port** (e.g., `5000`, `8000`, `3001`) and `VITE_API_BASE_URL` should be set via `.env` files.

> [!NOTE]
> **All hooks are ready to be migrated.** The `queryFn` in every hook currently does:
> ```ts
> await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));  // simulated delay
> return mockData;                              // тЖР replace with: axiosClient.get('/endpoint')
> ```
> Migration is a 1-line change per hook.

> [!NOTE]
> **No authentication flows exist yet** тАФ the token interceptor reads from `localStorage["token"]` but there's no login page, no auth context, no protected route guards, and no redirect on 401.

> [!TIP]
> **`staleTime` should be configured** once real APIs are in place. Currently queries refetch on every component mount (staleTime = 0 default). Consider setting `staleTime: 60_000` or per-query values in the backend integration phase.

> [!NOTE]
> **`App.tsx` is the default Vite boilerplate** тАФ it is never used in the routing tree. `main.tsx` goes directly to `AppRouter` which renders via `MainLayout` + `Outlet`.

> [!NOTE]
> The `Logs` page (`/operations/logs`) is a **stub** тАФ just a placeholder card with "coming soon" text, even though `logsData.ts` is rich (6 log entries with stack traces, metadata, levels, sources). This page needs its full UI built.

---

## Recommended Backend Stack Considerations

Based on the mock data types and the platform's domain (AI agent orchestration, deployments, CI/CD, governance):

- **Entities to model**: Projects, Workflows, Agents, Deployments, LogEntries, Approvals, CodeReviews, ArchitectureDecisions, Users, Roles, Teams, APIKeys, PromptTemplates, BillingRecords, SandboxEnvironments
- **Auth**: JWT-based (interceptor already reads `localStorage["token"]`)
- **Real-time**: Logs, Monitoring, and Agent execution status are candidates for WebSocket / SSE streams
- **File upload**: Sandbox live preview / demo builds may need blob/file storage
- **API structure**: RESTful is compatible with current axios client setup; GraphQL would require adding a client library

